# Testing

Vitest + React Testing Library. Tests live beside the code as `*.test.ts(x)`.

Write a test for every function with real logic. Cover the happy path, at least one
edge case, and one error case.

## Priority order
The things most worth testing here are the ones that would be clinically wrong if they
broke silently:

1. `buildSummary()` — correct values, correct provenance, verbatim parent text
2. Zod schema validation, especially LLM output parsing
3. FHIR mapping
4. Question definition integrity (see below)
5. Child component interaction — that a tap records the value it claims to

```ts
describe("buildSummary", () => {
  it("preserves parent free text verbatim", () => {
    const summary = buildSummary([parentTextResponse("He's been off food since Tuesday.")], session);
    expect(summary.parentNotes).toBe("He's been off food since Tuesday.");
  });

  it("marks proxy-captured responses as proxy", () => {
    const summary = buildSummary([response({ source: "proxy" })], session);
    expect(summary.items[0].source).toBe("proxy");
  });

  it("flags uniform response patterns as low confidence", () => {
    const summary = buildSummary(nineIdenticalYesResponses(), session);
    expect(summary.confidenceFlags).toContain("uniform_pattern");
  });

  it("makes no network calls", async () => {
    const spy = vi.spyOn(globalThis, "fetch");
    buildSummary(sampleResponses, session);
    expect(spy).not.toHaveBeenCalled();
  });
});
```

## Guard tests
Some constraints are worth asserting in CI because a well-meaning refactor could
quietly break them:

- Every question in `lib/questions/` has an i18n key present in **all** locale files
- Every question has a valid modality, a respondent, and at least one tier
- No question in the child flow has a free-text modality
- Suggestions cannot reach a session render path without an `approvedBy` field

```ts
it("every standard question is translated in every locale", () => {
  for (const q of STANDARD_QUESTIONS) {
    for (const locale of LOCALES) {
      expect(messages[locale]).toHaveProperty(q.i18nKey);
    }
  }
});
```

## Don't
- Don't test Tailwind classes or exact copy
- Don't snapshot-test child components — the illustrations will change constantly
- Don't call the real Anthropic API in tests; use a fixture response
